# asciigpt environment variables
# Copy to .env and fill in as needed:  cp .env.example .env
#
# asciigpt runs fully offline by default (the converter + the procedural
# generation backend) and needs NO configuration for that. You only need a
# value here to use a LIVE generation backend for arbitrary prompts.

# --- Live generation backend (used by: --backend command) ------------------
# A shell template asciigpt runs to produce the base image. Placeholders:
#   {prompt}  the text prompt   (asciigpt shell-quotes it for you)
#   {output}  the PNG path asciigpt expects the image at (shell-quoted)
#   {size}    the square pixel size (an integer)
# The command MUST write an image to {output}. Replace the example below with a
# real text-to-image CLI, or a rasterize render-to-file step:
#
#ASCIIGPT_IMAGE_COMMAND=txt2img --prompt {prompt} --size {size} --out {output}
